### 2. ATS Score Checker (New Page)
```
Route: /ats-score
Sidebar label: "ATS Score" (add under WORKSPACE section)
Icon: chart-bar or target icon

Layout: Two panel input + result output

INPUT PANEL (top):
- Resume input: Textarea or file upload (.pdf/.docx)
- Job Description input: Textarea (paste JD here)
- "Check Score" button

OUTPUT PANEL (below, shown after submit):
- Circular progress indicator showing Score: 0–100
  - 0–40: red
  - 41–70: yellow  
  - 71–100: green
- "Missing Keywords" section: red tag pills (keywords in JD not in resume)
- "Matched Keywords" section: green tag pills (keywords found in both)
- "Suggestions" section: numbered list of 3–5 actionable fixes
  e.g. "Add 'REST APIs' to your skills section"
  e.g. "Mention 'Agile' in your experience bullets"
- "Rescan" button (re-runs after user edits resume)

AI Prompt to use:
"You are an ATS resume scanner. Given the resume and job description below,
return a JSON object with:
- score: number 0-100
- matched_keywords: string[]
- missing_keywords: string[]
- suggestions: string[] (3-5 actionable fixes)
Only return JSON, no extra text."
```

