### 3. Application Tracker — Full Kanban Board (New Page)
```
Route: /applications
Sidebar label: "Applications" (add under WORKSPACE section)
Icon: layout-kanban icon

Layout: Full-width kanban board

5 Columns:
- Saved
- Applied
- Interview
- Offer
- Rejected

Each card shows:
- Company name + logo (favicon fallback)
- Role/Position title
- Date added
- Last action taken

Card interactions:
- Drag and drop between columns
- Click card → Side drawer opens with full details:
  - Company name, Role, JD link
  - Resume version used (dropdown from Resume Vault)
  - Notes textarea (editable)
  - Email history (list of cold emails sent for this job)
  - Status timeline (when it moved between stages)

Top bar:
- "Add Application" button → opens modal with fields:
  Company Name, Role, JD URL, Stage (default: Saved)
- Filter by: Stage, Date, Company

DB Schema (MongoDB):
{
  userId: ObjectId,
  company: String,
  role: String,
  jdUrl: String,
  stage: enum['saved','applied','interview','offer','rejected'],
  resumeVersionUsed: String,
  notes: String,
  emailHistory: [{ subject, sentAt, body }],
  createdAt: Date,
  updatedAt: Date
}
```

